  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study was to clarify the prognostic value of serum pro-Adrenomedullin level
      in neonatal sepsis. Eighty term and preterm neonates with sepsis were enrolled in this study.
      Eighty healthy matched neonates served as a control group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
